3:T6e3,You are a lead qualification assistant for [AGENT NAME], a real estate agent
specializing in [MARKET — e.g., Phoenix metro, $400K–$800K price range,
primary residences and move-up buyers].

You will receive a JSON object containing data about a new lead: their contact
info, CRM data, search behavior, any enrichment data, and their response to
the intake text message (if available).

Your task: score this lead from 1–10 based on their likelihood of transacting
in the next 90 days and their fit for this agent's practice.

SCORING CRITERIA:
- 8–10: Pre-approved or cash, actively searching, realistic price range,
  responsive, searching in agent's core markets. Needs immediate attention.
- 5–7: Some positive signals but incomplete picture. Pre-approval not
  confirmed, timeline vague, or price expectations uncertain.
- 2–4: Early research, unrealistic expectations, or signals of low intent
  (browsing Zillow for 6+ months with no engagement increase).
- 1: No response, invalid contact, or clearly not in buying stage.

OUTPUT — return exactly two fields, nothing else:

SCORE: [number 1–10]

RATIONALE: [One sentence explaining the top factor driving this score.
Be specific. Reference actual data points from the JSON, not generalities.
Example: "Pre-approved at $620K, actively searching for 3 weeks, responded
to intake text within 8 minutes asking about a specific listing."]

RULES:
- If intake text response is available, weight it heavily — it is the
  highest-signal data point
- Do not penalize leads for being early-stage if all other signals are strong
- If critical data is missing (no pre-approval data, no timeline), note this
  in rationale and score conservatively
- Never fabricate data points not present in the JSON0:["cEhtJqdwv2musQR5XQayr",[[["",{"children":["issues",{"children":["real-estate-lead-qualification-ai",{"children":["__PAGE__",{}]}]}]},"$undefined","$undefined",true],["",{"children":["issues",{"children":["real-estate-lead-qualification-ai",{"children":["__PAGE__",{},["$L1",["$","main",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-[#0a0a0a]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] px-6 py-4","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/","className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c] hover:text-[#d4b660] transition-colors","children":"← Operators Brief"}],["$","a",null,{"href":"/#signup","className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-widest uppercase bg-[#c9a84c] text-[#0a0a0a] px-4 py-2 hover:bg-[#d4b660] transition-colors","children":"Get All 52 Issues — $15/mo"}]]}]}],["$","article",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 mb-8","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c]","children":"Deep Dive"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"w-1 h-1 bg-[#2a2a2a] rounded-full"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550]","children":"Free Issue"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"w-1 h-1 bg-[#2a2a2a] rounded-full"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550]","children":"Real Estate"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"w-1 h-1 bg-[#2a2a2a] rounded-full"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550]","children":"10-min read"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-[32px] md:text-[44px] font-light leading-[1.1] tracking-tight text-[#f0ede8] mb-5","children":"The Realtor Who Qualified 200 Leads Without Answering a Single Call"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[18px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-12 border-l-2 border-[#c9a84c] pl-5","children":"A solo agent in a high-volume market was drowning in inbound leads. Most weren't serious. Calling every one was burning 30+ hours a week. Here's the CRM + AI qualification workflow she built — and what came out the other side."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"w-full h-px bg-[#1e1e1e] mb-12"}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-14","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c]","children":"01"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#5a5550]","children":"The Problem"}]]}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-[24px] font-light text-[#f0ede8] mb-5 leading-snug","children":"200 leads a month. 12 hours a week just answering inquiry calls."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"Sarah runs a solo real estate practice in the Phoenix metro. She spends about $4,500/month on lead generation across Zillow Premier Agent, Google Ads, and Facebook. On a good month, that produces 180–220 new inquiries. On a bad month, 90. Either way, the leads pour in."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"The problem wasn't the volume. It was the qualification call. Every lead got a 10–15 minute call to determine whether they were pre-approved, actively searching, realistic about price, and actually ready to move in the next 60–90 days. Of 200 leads, roughly 14 were worth her full attention. The other 186 needed to be disqualified, nurtured, or handed off."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"She was spending 12 hours every week on calls that produced 14 transactions-ready leads. The math was brutal: $320/hour of her time to produce a lead quality score she could have gotten another way."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-[#0d0d0d] border border-[#1e1e1e] p-5 my-8","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] font-mono text-[#5a5550] mb-2 uppercase tracking-wider","children":"The inefficiency in numbers:"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#f0ede8]","children":["200 leads × 12 min avg call = 40 hrs/month on qualification calls.",["$","br",null,{}],"14 serious buyers found. ",["$","span",null,{"className":"text-[#c9a84c]","children":"That's 2.8 hours per qualified lead — before a single showing."}]]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"The goal wasn't to eliminate the human relationship. It was to stop spending 40 hours a month figuring out who deserved one."}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-14","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c]","children":"02"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#5a5550]","children":"The Workflow"}]]}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-[24px] font-light text-[#f0ede8] mb-5 leading-snug","children":"The 4-layer qualification system"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-8","children":"This workflow runs inside Follow Up Boss (her CRM), uses Zapier for automation triggers, Claude API for scoring, and a pre-built email sequence for nurture. Setup time: about 3 weeks of part-time work, mostly configuring the CRM logic and prompt refinement."}],[["$","div","0",{"className":"mb-6 border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#c9a84c] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Layer 1"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Follow Up Boss + Clearbit/People Data Labs"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"px-5 py-4","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[15px] font-medium text-[#f0ede8] mb-3","children":"Lead intake + automatic data enrichment"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"Every new lead that enters the CRM is automatically enriched with available public data: LinkedIn presence, estimated income bracket (where available), neighborhood signals from their search behavior on Zillow. Zapier pulls what it can and adds it to the contact record as custom fields. This takes 90 seconds per lead and requires no manual input. Enrichment data quality is imperfect — but even partial signals improve the AI score meaningfully."}]]}]]}],["$","div","1",{"className":"mb-6 border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#c9a84c] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Layer 2"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Follow Up Boss drip + Twilio"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"px-5 py-4","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[15px] font-medium text-[#f0ede8] mb-3","children":"Automated text + email intake sequence"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"Within 90 seconds of a new lead entering, they receive a personalized text: \"Hi [Name], it's Sarah — I saw you were looking at homes in [Area]. Quick question: are you working with a lender yet, or still in the early research phase?\" Responses feed back into the CRM. Leads who respond within 2 hours are flagged; leads who don't respond in 24 hours enter a 5-email nurture sequence. The text response data is the single highest-signal input for the AI scoring step."}]]}]]}],["$","div","2",{"className":"mb-6 border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#c9a84c] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Layer 3"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Claude API — lead scoring prompt"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"px-5 py-4","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[15px] font-medium text-[#f0ede8] mb-3","children":"AI lead qualification scoring"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"Once a lead has either responded to the intake text or completed the nurture sequence, Zapier sends their full contact record (enrichment data + response text + search behavior from the CRM) to Claude. Claude returns a 1–10 qualification score and a one-sentence rationale. Scores are written back to the CRM as a custom field. Leads scoring 7+ get a calendar booking link from Sarah immediately. Leads scoring 4–6 enter a longer nurture sequence. Leads scoring 1–3 are tagged for quarterly re-engagement only."}]]}]]}],["$","div","3",{"className":"mb-6 border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#c9a84c] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Layer 4"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Follow Up Boss smart lists + Zapier"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"px-5 py-4","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[15px] font-medium text-[#f0ede8] mb-3","children":"Automated follow-up based on score"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"Each score tier triggers a different follow-up track. 7–10: Sarah gets an SMS alert with the lead's score and rationale, and they receive a booking link within 4 minutes of scoring. 4–6: 12-email sequence over 90 days, increasingly specific to their search criteria, with a re-score trigger if they click any listing link. 1–3: Monthly market update email only, with a re-qualification trigger at 90 days. No manual steps required for tiers 2 and 3."}]]}]]}]]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-14","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c]","children":"03"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#5a5550]","children":"The Prompt"}]]}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-[24px] font-light text-[#f0ede8] mb-5 leading-snug","children":"The exact lead scoring prompt — copy-paste ready"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-6","children":"This is the full system prompt. The user message is a JSON object containing the lead's CRM data. Adjust the scoring criteria and market details to match your practice."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"relative","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"absolute top-0 left-0 right-0 h-8 bg-[#0d0d0d] border border-[#1e1e1e] border-b-0 flex items-center px-4 gap-2","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#1e1e1e]"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#1e1e1e]"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#1e1e1e]"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"ml-auto font-mono text-[10px] text-[#5a5550]","children":"SYSTEM PROMPT — Lead Scoring"}]]}],["$","pre",null,{"className":"mt-8 bg-[#0a0a0a] border border-[#1e1e1e] p-5 text-[12px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap font-mono","children":"$3"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#5a5550] mt-4 leading-relaxed","children":"Each scoring call uses roughly 600–800 input tokens (the lead data JSON) and 80–100 output tokens. At claude-3-5-sonnet pricing, that's about $0.007 per lead. For 200 leads/month: $1.40. The API cost is irrelevant relative to the time saved."}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-14","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c]","children":"04"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#5a5550]","children":"Tool Stack + Timeline"}]]}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-[24px] font-light text-[#f0ede8] mb-5 leading-snug","children":"What it costs to run this and how long setup takes"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"overflow-x-auto mb-8","children":["$","table",null,{"className":"w-full border border-[#1e1e1e] text-[13px]","children":[["$","thead",null,{"children":["$","tr",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d]","children":[["$","th",null,{"className":"text-left px-4 py-3 font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Tool"}],["$","th",null,{"className":"text-left px-4 py-3 font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Purpose"}],["$","th",null,{"className":"text-right px-4 py-3 font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Cost/mo"}]]}]}],["$","tbody",null,{"className":"divide-y divide-[#1e1e1e]","children":[["$","tr","0",{"className":"hover:bg-[#0d0d0d] transition-colors ","children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#9a9590]","children":"Follow Up Boss"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#5a5550]","children":"CRM, smart lists, drip sequences"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono text-[#9a9590]","children":"$$69"}]]}],["$","tr","1",{"className":"hover:bg-[#0d0d0d] transition-colors ","children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#9a9590]","children":"Zapier (Professional)"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#5a5550]","children":"Automation triggers + webhooks"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono text-[#9a9590]","children":"$$49"}]]}],["$","tr","2",{"className":"hover:bg-[#0d0d0d] transition-colors ","children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#9a9590]","children":"Twilio"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#5a5550]","children":"SMS intake + follow-up texts"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono text-[#9a9590]","children":"~$18"}]]}],["$","tr","3",{"className":"hover:bg-[#0d0d0d] transition-colors ","children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#9a9590]","children":"Claude API"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#5a5550]","children":"Lead scoring (200 leads/mo)"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono text-[#9a9590]","children":"$$1.40"}]]}],["$","tr","4",{"className":"hover:bg-[#0d0d0d] transition-colors ","children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#9a9590]","children":"Clearbit (enrichment)"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#5a5550]","children":"Contact data enrichment"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono text-[#9a9590]","children":"$$99"}]]}],["$","tr","5",{"className":"hover:bg-[#0d0d0d] transition-colors border-t border-[#2a2a2a]","children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#f0ede8] font-medium","children":"Total"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#5a5550]","children":""}],["$","td",null,{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono text-[#c9a84c] font-medium","children":"$$236/mo"}]]}]]}]]}]}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[18px] font-light text-[#f0ede8] mb-5","children":"Implementation timeline (part-time, ~10 hrs/week)"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-3","children":[["$","div","Week 1",{"className":"border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d] p-5","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-2","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#c9a84c] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Week 1"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-[14px] font-medium text-[#f0ede8]","children":"CRM audit + intake sequence setup"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"Clean your CRM, set up the intake text trigger in Follow Up Boss, connect Twilio. Build the 5-email nurture sequence for non-responders."}]]}],["$","div","Week 2",{"className":"border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d] p-5","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-2","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#c9a84c] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Week 2"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-[14px] font-medium text-[#f0ede8]","children":"Data enrichment + Zapier automation"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"Connect your enrichment tool. Build the Zap that fires on new lead creation, pulls enrichment data, and writes custom fields back to the CRM."}]]}],["$","div","Week 3",{"className":"border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d] p-5","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-2","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#c9a84c] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Week 3"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-[14px] font-medium text-[#f0ede8]","children":"Claude scoring integration + score-based routing"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"Connect the scoring Zap (CRM data → Claude API → score back to CRM). Build smart lists by score tier. Set up tier-specific follow-up tracks. Test with 10 real leads."}]]}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-14","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"f